  --------------
  Maven Metadata
  --------------

Maven Metadata

  When Maven creates a JAR-style artifact (including JARs, WARs, EARs,
  RARs, and most custom JAR-like packages), it includes two pieces of
  metadata: the POM used to build the artifact, and a small properties
  file containing the artifact's <<<groupId>>>, <<<artifactId>>>, and
  <<<version>>> attributes. This metadata is stored in the
  <<<META-INF/maven/<groupId>/<artifactId>/>>> directory by the JAR
  archiver.
  
  These tools use the file <<<pom.properties>>> from this directory
  to identify the versions of artifacts that are actually in use. The
  tools load properties files from the running system using
  {{{http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/ClassLoader.html#getResource(java.lang.String)}ClassLoader resources}}
  or, in a webapp, {{{http://java.sun.com/javaee/5/docs/api/javax/servlet/ServletContext.html#getResource(java.lang.String)}ServletContext resources}}.
  
* Example <<<pom.properties>>>

+-------------------------------+
#Generated by Maven
#Sat Jul 11 01:13:49 EDT 2009
version=1.0-SNAPSHOT
groupId=ca.grimoire.maven
artifactId=maven-taglib
+-------------------------------+

